Comments:
The definition of "related" is subjective - throughout the study my perception definitely changed, or at least, the reasons the sequences were deemed related became less and less consistent. i.e. sometimes it was harmony driven, other times it was key driven, other times it was just intuition etc. - so many variables/factors

Concerns: a few of my sequences did not play clearly - around number 250 (approx.) - I wasn't sure if this was intentional so my perception for a few of these sequences was definitely off. 

Perhaps timed breaks are more effective? I found that giving myself longer breaks made the next set of sequences easier to hear as I'd given my brain/ears ample time to reset.

Whatever the outcome, I think my progress definitely deteriorated the further into the test I went. It became harder to differentiate everything and think clearly.
